rComments: There is really nothing I can find wrong with the class I'm taking with Rodgers now, and most of that is due to the man himself. Joel is a super friendly, relatable, compassionate and hilarious guy. He puts in a lot of effort to connect with the students by remembering names, asking for their input & making the best jokes to keep the class engaged!
Had a really rough semester but Joel was an amazing professor. He used familiar pop culture references to explain content and I looked forward to every class!

Wonderful, caring professor with amazing sense of humour. He really does care about his class and is so personable. Extremely intelligent; his close-readings are so captivating. Encourages class participation but may pick on students to get them to "go deeper" in analyses. Still a great professor. Highly recommended.

He truly is a wonderful prof to have, especially for introductory courses! Lectures are always interesting and filled with info you'll use in the course and in the future. His marking is fair, he gives clear and helpful feedback and a variety of opportunities to prove yourself. The assignments and exams are doable and fair! He's great overall!

I just started taking his class and man! He has such a positive attitude every class, and its a 3 hr class that starts at 9 so thats not so easy. He takes time to get to know the students names, and it makes a difference bc it allows people to feel comfortable. I hope the rest of the semester goes well with Rodgers.

Best. Professor.  I have no other words to describe him. He is so smart and really knows what he's talking about. He takes the time and learns everyones name even in a lecture with over 40 students- he is a phenomenal teacher and I took a class just because he was teaching it.
